---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "March 11, 2026";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — chrod"
  description="Privacy Policy for chrod developer portfolio."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-32 text-slate-300">
    <a
      href="/"
      class="mb-10 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-500 transition-colors hover:text-red-400"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="14"
        height="14"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
      >
        <path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"></path>
      </svg>
      Back to home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold text-slate-100">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-12 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="space-y-10 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          1. Introduction
        </h2>
        <p>
          Welcome to <strong class="text-slate-200">chrod</strong> (the "Portfolio"),
          operated by Carlos Hernández ("I", "me", or "my"). This Privacy Policy explains
          how I collect, use, and protect any information you provide when you visit
          this website or contact me through the contact form or via WhatsApp.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          By using this website, you agree to the terms described in this
          policy. If you do not agree, please do not use this website.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          2. Information I Collect
        </h2>
        <p>
          I only collect information you voluntarily provide through the contact
          form or via WhatsApp:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-slate-400">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-slate-300">Name</strong> — to address you properly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-slate-300">Email address</strong> — to respond to
            your inquiry (contact form only).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-slate-300">Phone number</strong> — visible when you
            initiate contact via WhatsApp.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-slate-300">Message</strong> — the content of your
            inquiry.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          I do not collect any data automatically (no cookies, no tracking
          scripts, no analytics) unless explicitly stated otherwise.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          3. How I Use Your Information
        </h2>
        <p>The information you provide is used exclusively to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-slate-400">
          <li>Respond to your message or inquiry.</li>
          <li>
            Follow up on potential collaboration or project opportunities.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          I will never sell, rent, or share your personal information with third
          parties for marketing purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          4. Data Retention
        </h2>
        <p>
          I retain your contact information only as long as necessary to respond
          to your inquiry or maintain a professional relationship. You can
          request deletion of your data at any time by contacting me directly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          5. Third-Party Services
        </h2>
        <p>
          This website may use third-party services for form handling, hosting,
          or communication (e.g., EmailJs, Netlify, WhatsApp / Meta Platforms,
          Inc.). These services may process your data according to their own
          privacy policies. I recommend reviewing their respective policies for
          more information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          6. Your Rights
        </h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-slate-400">
          <li>Access the personal data I hold about you.</li>
          <li>Request correction or deletion of your data.</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent for any data processing at any time.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To exercise any of these rights, please contact me using the
          information below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">7. Security</h2>
        <p>
          I take reasonable measures to protect any information you submit.
          However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure,
          and I cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">
          8. Changes to This Policy
        </h2>
        <p>
          I may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will
          be reflected on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the
          website after changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated
          policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-100">9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how I handle
          your data, please contact me at:
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 font-medium text-slate-200">
          Carlos Hernández — <a
            href="mailto:chrod.dev@gmail.com"
            class="text-red-400 hover:underline">chrod.dev@gmail.com</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
